Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,earthquake: n.  地震\N\NLesson 42 Recording an earthquake\N\N记录地震\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.35,0:00:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,First listen and then answer the following question.\N\N听录音,然后回答以下问题.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.19,0:00:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,earthquake: n.  地震\N\NWhat does a pen have to do?to record on paper the vibrations generated by an earthquake?\N\N怎样才能用笔?在纸上记录下地震引起的振动?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.87,0:00:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,earthquake: n.  地震\N\NAn earthquake comes like a thief in the night,without warning.\N\N地震就像夜间的小偷,不打招呼就来了.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.45,0:00:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It was necessary, therefore,\N\N因此,有必要,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.59,0:00:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,slumber: v.  睡眠\N\Nto invent instruments that neither slumbered nor slept.\N\N发明一种仪器,既不打盹儿,也不睡觉.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.92,0:00:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Some devices were quite simple.\N\N有些装置非常简单.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.38,0:00:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One,for instance, consisted of rods of various lengths and thicknesses,\N\N例如,有一种装置是由一些长短、粗细不同的木棒组成,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.91,0:00:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ninepin: n.  九柱戏中的木柱\N\Nwhich would stand up on end like ninepins.\N\N就像九柱戏的木棒一样竖立着.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.36,0:00:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When a shock came, it shook the rigid table upon which these stood.\N\N一旦有地震,就会震动竖立在坚硬的桌子上的木棒.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.38,0:00:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If it were gentle, only the more unstable rods fell.\N\N如果地震轻微,只有不稳定的木棒倒下;\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.01,0:00:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If it were severe, they all fell.\N\N如果地震剧烈,所有的木棒都会倒下.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.26,0:00:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus the rods,by falling,and by the direction in which they fell,\N\N木棒倒下的多少和倒下的方向,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.25,0:01:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,slumber: v.  睡眠\N\Nrecorded for the slumbering scientist,\N\N能在科学家未醒时为科学家记录下,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.82,0:01:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the strength of a shock that was too weak to waken him,\N\N轻微的不能惊醒他的地震强度,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.34,0:01:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and the direction from which it came.\N\N以及地震方向.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.05,0:01:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But instruments far more delicate than that were needed,\N\N但是,需要有比这种装置精细得多的仪器,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.16,0:01:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,if any really serious advance was to be made\N\N才能取得真正重大的进展\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.18,0:01:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The ideal to be aimed at,\N\N理想的目标是,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.24,0:01:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,was to devise an instrument that could record with a pen on paper,\N\N设计出这样一种仪器:它能用笔在纸上记录下,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.81,0:01:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the movements of the ground or of the table as the quake passed by.\N\N地震发生时大地和桌子的运动情况.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.48,0:01:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,While I write my pen moves,but the paper keeps still.\N\N我写字时,笔是移动的,纸是静止的.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.82,0:01:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,With practice,no doubt,\N\N毫无疑问,经过练习,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.85,0:01:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I could in time learn to write by holding the pen still while the paper moved.\N\N我最终能够学会笔不动而纸动来写字.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.82,0:01:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds a silly suggestion,\N\N这种想法听起来似乎愚有可及,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.44,0:01:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but that was precisely the idea adopted in some of the early instruments,\N\N但是早期记录地震波的仪器,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.39,0:01:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,earthquake: n.  地震, seismometer: n.  地震仪\N\N(seismometers) for recording earthquake waves.\N\N(测震仪)正是采用了这种思路.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.81,0:01:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,penholder: n.  笔杆\N\NBut when table, penholder and paper are all moving,\N\N可是,当桌子,夹笔装置,纸都在移动时,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.95,0:02:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,how is it possible to write legibly?\N\N怎么能书写得清楚呢?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.01,0:02:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The key to a solution of that problem lay in an everyday observation.\N\N可以从我们的日常生活观察中找到这个问题的答案.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.53,0:02:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does a person sta- nding in a bus or tra- in tend to fall when a sudden start is made?\N\N一个人站在公共汽车或火车上,当车突然开动时,他为什么会倾倒呢?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.33,0:02:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It is because his feet move on,but his head stays still.\N\N这是因为他的脚动了,而他的头保持着静止.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.42,0:02:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A simple experiment will help us a little further.\N\N再做一个简单的实验可以帮助我们进一步理解这个问题.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.46,0:02:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tie a heavy weight at the end of a long piece of string.\N\N把一个重物拴在一根长绳子的一端,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.06,0:02:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,With the hand held high in the air,\N\N把手高高举在空中,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.54,0:02:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,hold the string so that the weight nearly touches the ground.\N\N握住绳子,让重物几乎接触地面.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.98,0:02:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now move the hand to and fro and around but not up and down.\N\N然后把手前后左右及旋转摆动,但不要上下摆动.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.20,0:02:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be found that the weight moves but slightly or not at all.\N\N结果会发现,重物是动了,但动得很小,甚至根本没动.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.67,0:02:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine a pen attached to the weight in such a way,\N\N假定把一支笔拴在重物上,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that its point rests upon a piece of paper on the floor.\N\N笔尖落在地板上的一张纸上.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.25,0:03:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,earthquake: n.  地震\N\NImagine an earthquake shock shaking the floor,the paper,you and your hand.\N\N假定地震发生了,地板、纸、你和你的手都会动.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.20,0:03:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In the midst of all this movement,the weight and the pen would be still.\N\N重物和笔都却不运动.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.74,0:03:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But as the paper moved from side to side under the pen point,\N\N由于纸在笔尖下来回运动,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.88,0:03:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,its movement would be recorded in ink upon its surface.\N\N纸的表面就会用墨水记录下地板运动的情况.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.48,0:03:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It was upon this principle that the first instruments were made,\N\N根据这一原理,制造出了最初的地震仪器,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.67,0:03:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,drum: n.  鼓状物\N\Nbut the paper was wrapped round a drum which rotated slowly.\N\N但是纸是卷在慢慢旋转的圆筒上的.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.02,0:03:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as all was still,the pen drew a straight line,\N\N只要一切都是静止的,笔就会划出一条直线,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.95,0:03:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,drum: n.  鼓状物, wriggle: v.  扭动\N\Nbut while the drum was being shaken,the line that the pen was drawing wriggled from side to side.\N\N但是,圆筒受到震动时,笔所画出的线就会左右摆动.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.23,0:03:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The apparatus thus described,however,\N\N然而,这里所说的仪器,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.87,0:03:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,records only the horizontal component of the wave movement,\N\N记录下来的只是地震波运动中的水平部分,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.78,0:03:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,which is,in fact, much more complicated.\N\N地震波的运动实际比这要复杂得多.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.97,0:03:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If we could actually see the path described by a particle,\N\N假如我们真能看到一个沙粒分子的运动轨迹,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.92,0:03:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,such as a sand grain in the rock,\N\N诸如岩石中的一人沙粒分子.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.38,0:03:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,bluebottle: n.  绿头苍蝇\N\Nit would be more like that of a bluebottle buzzing round the room,\N\N那就像一只嗡嗡叫的绿头苍蝇在屋内飞行的轨迹,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.11,0:04:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be up and down,to and fro and from side to side.\N\N呈现出上上下下、来来回回、左左右右3种性质的运动.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.32,0:04:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,graph: n.  图表\N\NInstruments have been devised and can be so placed,that all three elements can be recorded in different graphs.\N\N已经设计出了一些仪器,它按照一定的安放方式,就可测绘出这三种运动的曲线图.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,earthquake: n.  地震\N\NWhen the instrument is situated at more than 700 miles from the earthquake centre,\N\N如果把这种仪器安装在距震源700多英里远的地方,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.78,0:04:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,graph: n.  图表, graphic: adj.  图示的\N\Nthe graphic record shows,\N\N曲线记录就能显示出,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.08,0:04:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,three waves arriving one after the other at short intervals.\N\N前后相间的这3种地震波.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.54,0:04:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The first records the arrival of longitudinal vibrations,\N\N首先记录下的是纵向波的到达,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.44,0:04:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The second marks the arrival of transverse vibrations,\N\N然后记录下的是横向波的到达,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.89,0:04:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,which travel more slowly and arrive several minutes after the first.\N\N横向波比纵向波传播得慢,在纵向波到达几分钟后才能到达.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.45,0:04:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,These two have travelled through the earth.\N\N这两种波都是穿过地球而来的.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.54,0:04:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was from the study of these that so much was learnt about the interior of the earth.\N\N正是从这两种波的研究中,我们可以了解到地球内部的许多情况.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.04,0:04:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The third,or main wave is the slowest,\N\N第三种波,即主波,是最慢的,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.06,0:04:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and has travelled round the earth through the surface rocks.\N\N是围绕地球通过表面岩石传来的.\N\N